cdata.name: Miner One token
cdata.desc: Miner One is a different breed of mining operation. It can´t be labelled a mining pool, because it doesn’t rely on participants’ computing power. It can´t be catalogued as the familiar and standart mining companies we are used to, as it doesn’t rent hashing power and charge administrative fees. The main difference and what's at the basis of the Miner One business model is the ERC20 MIO Token, which represents membership in the Miner One community and a share of what the Miner One mines.
